cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with routing protocols in mobile ad hoc networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a secured approach using triple factor and cryptographic algorithms to ensure security, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the performance of routing protocols and proposes a triple factor approach to improve it, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the computation of trust and reputation, which falls under the scope of information theory. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a solution to improve the performance of routing protocols, which falls under the scope of software engineering.
